author: FRONTLINE PBS | Official
description:
A Venezuelan family navigates the shifting legal landscape for immigrants and asylum seekers under the Trump administration in this video drawn from the new ProPublica/FRONTLINE documentary "Status: Venezuelan."

Watch the full documentary starting Dec. 9 via @ProPublica & @frontline.

Read more: https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/article/venezuela-family-immigration-policy-donald-trump-florida/

"Status: Venezuelan" is a ProPublica production that is part of the FRONTLINE FEATURES initiative. The director is Mauricio Rodríguez Pons. The senior producers are Frank Koughan and Lisa Riordan Seville. Almudena Toral is ProPublica’s executive producer and ProPublica’s editor-in-chief is Stephen Engelberg. The editor-in-chief and executive producer of FRONTLINE is Raney Aronson-Rath.
title: A Venezuelan Family Fights to Stay in the US Legally (documentary excerpt) | FRONTLINE/@ProPublica
